<section id="conventions-used" version="5.0" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
                                             xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                                             xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" >
  <title>Conventions Used</title>
  <para>
    Throughout the manual,
    particular conventions are used to improve readability and
    clarity:
  </para>
  <section id="typesetting-conventions">
    <title>Typesetting Conventions</title>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Menu paths are shown with a grey background:
          
          <para>
            <emphasis role="menuPath">Test</emphasis>--&gt;<emphasis role="menuPath">Open</emphasis>
          </para>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Buttons and menu options are italicized and in inverted commas:
          
          <para>
            ”<emphasis>OK</emphasis>”
          </para>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Input statements are shown in typewriter format:
          
          <para>
            <emphasis role="input">Hello</emphasis>
          </para>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Keyboard shortcuts and commands are in French brackets:
          
          <para>
            <emphasis role="input">»ENTER«</emphasis>
          </para>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    <para>
      In addition, important warnings and informative tips are
      marked as follows:
    </para>
    <para>
      <para role="warning">This is a warning.</para> 
      <para role="tip">This is a tip.</para>
    </para>
  </section>
</section>